rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0001
rows.name:
So the World Tree didn't budge an inch
even after a Divine Beast bumped right into it?
What must that thing be made of?!

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0002
rows.name:
As a botanist, naturally the World Tree
piques my curiosity to no end!

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0003
rows.name:
What I wouldn't give to examine it for
myself someday... I could take young
Elis along too, do a bit of fieldwork.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0004
rows.name:
Elis is this kid in town who takes
care of the trees.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0005
rows.name:
He's got quite an appreciation for
nature, and he even told me he wants
to be a botanist when he's older.

rows.label: tlk41700126_03_msg0006
rows.name:
So I figure it's my duty to be a
good example for him, you know.
Set him on the right track.
